Project Director
03 May 2014 06:44 AM - UAE
.
An Exciting opportunity to work for WSP in the Middle East as a Project Director (with marine background). The Project Director is a senior management role; accountable for contributing to the strategic leadership, operational performance, technical and people leadership of complex large scale multi disciplinary projects across WSP Middle East (ME) The role holder must take a 'hands on' approach to all aspects of the role.
Responsibilities
Project Leadership • Lead and project manage the successful delivery of complex large scale high quality multi disciplinary projects • Ensure that projects adhere to Project Lifecycle • Accountable for the contractual relationship between the business and the client; taking the process from proposal to contract, utilising the advice of the support functions• Engage with the CRCs at the Prospect stage through to completion to ensure the most cost efficient delivery of their projects• Ensure proactive project planning, stakeholder and risk management takes place across projects• Supervise the team to identify, assess and manage major project risk and secure the best commercial return from the projects in their portfolio• To ensure statutory and regulatory requirements are met• Accountable for delivery to project P&L budgets, forecasts and working capital targets for projects• Accountable for the accurate and timely recognition of revenue for projects• Accountable for overseeing and delivering the process of working capital management from inception to completion within set deadlines; This includes the timing of invoicing, the review of Work in Progress (WIP) and the collection of outstanding invoices from clients whilst utilising the advice of the support functions as necessary• Contribute to the completion of monthly management project reports to be issued by set deadlineBusiness Leadership• Responsible for the leadership and support of their team• Ensure that Health & Safety is embedded into all work practices in line with company policies• Ensure the right resources are utilised effectively at the right time across their team and projects. Including engaging with the Complimentary Resource Centres (CRCs) to ensure that communication and design processes are continually improved• Input into recruitment and selection strategies• Contribute to project teams inductions, performance management reviews and personal development plans that support the development of individuals and the business• Contribute to succession planning and career development across their team• Support the development and delivery of training and awareness session as required• Contribute to the development and drive the implementation of the business strategy• Provide project and team updates for the development of the Operational Leadership Team (OLT) monthly reports.• Attend and contribute to quarterly senior management meetings• Attend and lead team and project meetings, cascade relevant information and encourage feedback from team• Contribute to the setting and delivering P&L Business Unit (BU) budget and forecasts• Engage with peer group and contribute to industry events and associations• Lead by example and ensure QMS and Project lifecycle compliance across projects• Provide leadership and guidance on the companies approach to Sustainability and ensure that the Sustainability strategy is implemented across projectsBusiness Development• Proactively support business development activities through participation in external market profile raising activities and functions• Actively develop external and internal client relationships• Proactively co sell other WSP ME services and where applicable the wider business• Contribute to the Global Account Management (GAM) and Key Account Management (KAM) programmes, with the aim of increasing client intelligence to develop win solutions and support unique selling points for prospects• Authority to manage prospect decisions in line with the companies Prospect to Project process. • Act as the Prospect Director on selected prospects• Responsible for the 'Prospect to Project Process' for lead projects and overseeing the process for direct reports.• Provide technical leadership to respond to prequalification documents, Request for Price (RFPs) and other client inquiries• Responsible for providing financial build-up of resource and lump sum pricing items for prospects where requiredTechnical• Keep up to date with industry developments with respect to own discipline, other disciplines and engineering innovations and developments on a global scale• Support the technical capabilities of the BU and project team• Maintain contact with key technical leaders across WSP offices and around the world• Provide support and guidance to Technical Working Group (TWG)• Initiate and facilitate technical solutions on projects• Drive innovation and utilise technological advancement• Contribute to and lead design peer reviews in alignment with the QMS system
Requirements
• BEng / BSc (Hon) or equivalent degree with minimum 15 years post graduate experience• Member of associated Professional body• NA preferred although not essential• Preference to candidates with Master-Planning & Buildings Concept experience• Experience and proven ability to lead and project manage an engineering team and multi-disciplinary projects• Experience of MS Office Suite of Programmes• Comprehensive experience in associated discipline software. • Experience and proven ability to lead and project manage an engineering team and multi-disciplinary projects• Experience of MS Office Suite of Programmes• Comprehensive e (more...)
